Yung Yizzo’s music style is influenced by the East Coast’s lyrical rhyme scheme with a twist of West Coast feel.
He started rapping for fun at the age of 16 in a friends’ basement studio setup. Through childhood and present day friend, Blake Bryant of Deblu, is where his passion for music began to grow. “He gave me my first taste of accomplishment in recording music and making a track.” In 2008, he created a music group with cousins Charles Daniel and John Alleyene, which they called NGP (in remembrance of family friend Roy Jenkins killed in 2005.) Having performed at a few venues with NGP, the group songs got off to a good start and received positive feedback. With more and more exposure in the music industry, Yung Yizzo’s drive to make music his life only continued to grow but he soon found himself having to make a tough choice. Needing financial stability, music could not be a life priority at the time and Yung Yizzo joined the U.S. Navy early 2010. Later that year, he crossed paths with a few new friends in the military who had the same passion to make music and they all decided to put their diverse talents together making a group called Serious Nerd Gang (SNG), a group in which Yung Yizzo is still an active part of.
The diversity within SNG helped Yung Yizzo’s versatility in music expand and has allowed him to do opening performances for major artists such as: Rich Homie Quan, Rocko, French Montana, and Pitbull, to name a few.
His Hit Single “Chill” was recently released and is now available on iTunes. With mixtape “They Doubted Me” already out, Yung Yizzo continues to create new music.
